This file contains a description of a supplemental material accompanying the
IEEE Trans. Comp. manuscript ``Speculatively Redundant Continued Logarithm 
Representation'' (DOI: 10.1109/TC.2010.110).

These files are being republished here as they are no longer available from
IEEE Xplore.

Contents:

* TC.2010.110.proof.pdf (size 108,543 B): This is a PDF document titled
  ``Proof of Interior Containment''. This document forms an appendix to
  the manuscript text. It contains a proof of interior containment of
  the speculatively redundant representation proposed in the manuscript.
  The appendix has been separated to make the manuscript meet page count
  limits set by IEEE Trans. Comp.

* TC.2010.110.results.pdf (size 125,480 B): This is a PDF document titled
  ``Quantitative Results''. It provides results of a comparison between
  the speculatively redundant continued logarithms, proposed in the manuscript,
  and some other representations. These results accompany the manuscript
  to illustrate the hypotheses discussed in the manuscript (Sec. 5,
  ``Practical Results of Redundancy'').
